This benchmark measures write latency and throughput for a prototype of 'n' processes performing one
to one writes across 2 scif nodes. The following steps need to be followed to run the benchmark:

  1. Copy the files scif_multiproc.cpp, timer.cpp, get_vals.sh and makefile to a folder on the server.
  
  2. Open the makefile and update the FILE_PATH to the complete path of the folder and update default 
     values of other parameters described in the makefile. This step is optional as parameter values
     can also be specified while running make.
      
  3. To run the benchmark: 
     -> for a single data size 
        a)with the host as sender:
        
            with default values: 
            -> make run_host TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id>
            
            with parameters specified:
            -> make run_host TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id> NUM_PROCS=<number_of_processes> MSG_SIZE=<msg_size_bytes> RMA_TYPE=<m(for scif_mmap) / a(for scif_writeto) / v(for scif_vwriteto)> FILE_PATH=<complete_folder_path>
            
        b)with the mic as sender:
        
            with default values: 
            -> make run_mic MIC=<mic_name> TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id>
            
            with parameters specified:
            -> make run_mic MIC=<mic_name> TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id> NUM_PROCS=<number_of_processes> MSG_SIZE=<msg_size_bytes> RMA_TYPE=<m(for scif_mmap) / a(for scif_writeto) / v(for scif_vwriteto)> FILE_PATH=<complete_folder_path>
            
     -> for data sizes from 8 bytes upto a specified data size. Values will be written to a file "vals_raw_num_procs_target_node_rma_type" in the same folder.  
        a)with host as sender:
        
            with default values: 
            -> make getvals_host TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id>
            
            with parameters specified:
            -> make getvals_host TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id> NUM_PROCS=<number_of_processes> MAX_MSG_SIZE=<msg_size_bytes> RMA_TYPE=<m(for scif_mmap) / a(for scif_writeto) / v(for scif_vwriteto)> FILE_PATH=<complete_folder_path>
            
        b)with mic as sender:
        
            with default values: 
            -> make getvals_mic MIC=<mic_name> TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id>
            
            with parameters specified:
            -> make getvals_mic MIC=<mic_name> TARGET_NODE=<target_scif_id> NUM_PROCS=<number_of_processes> MAX_MSG_SIZE=<msg_size_bytes> RMA_TYPE=<m(for scif_mmap) / a(for scif_writeto) / v(for scif_vwriteto)> FILE_PATH=<complete_folder_path>